Dear Elementary Families,

Here’s a brief update for tomorrow!!!

Friday Dismissal Times:

Park and Pickup Vehicles 12:15

Walkers 12:25

Driveline 12:30 (note: once your student is in your car you may pull into the left lane to exit campus)

Lunch:

We understand that there are circumstances that happen which result in the student not bringing their lunch to school. Beginning Monday, September 14th, the office will have a table set up for these occasional circumstances. Please make sure the student's name is clearly visible. Your student's classroom will be notified and it will be the student's responsibility to retrieve the lunch.

post_text:
Dear Puma Families,

As per the outcome of our reopening meeting this morning, it has been determined that we will officially open for in person instruction on Tuesday, September 8, 2020. The particulars of how we will resume will be sent out early next week to include details outlining our school’s mitigation plan, schedules and other important information.

Due to preparation for in person instruction all Zoom Live Learning sessions for K-6 will be canceled as of Wednesday, September 2, 2020. The Google Classroom platform will continue until the end of next week.

We want to ensure the safety of all staff, students and community members, so procedures and protocols will be outlined to ensure that we are meeting the needs of all stakeholders.

Sequoia Pathway Administration

post_text:
Elementary wants to have some fun during the second week of school, so we are having a Spirit Week! Below are the following themed days!

Movie Madness Monday: Dress up like your favorite movie character.
Totally Tourist Tuesday: Dress up like you’re going on vacation to somewhere you’ve always wanted to go, or have already been to.
Wacky Wears Wednesday: Dress wacky, zany, or otherwise cooky.
Throwback Thursday: Dress up from your (or your parents) favorite era.
Future Friday: Dress up for the job you want to have when you grow up!

Wear your outfits during your Live Learning Sessions, or post them right here to our page!

Elementary Admin will be popping into the LIve Learning Sessions to see who has the most spirit! Let’s have a fun week, and a great year!!!

With the Governor's executive order delaying the start of K-12 schools, do you, or someone you know with children attending one of the small public district or charter schools without their own online program, want to help a child get a head start in school this coming semester? We have over 2 decades (established August 16, 1999) of high quality online education experience and student outcomes (highest SAT scores in AZ online education) to offer you. Don't reinvent the wheel or spend a ton of money on a less experienced online program option. We are here to help all Arizona students, their families, and communities, in kick starting this upcoming school year. Feel free to reach out to discuss what we offer.

Mark Plitzuweit, CEO Edkey, Inc.

We reported last week that Edkey Inc. was selected as a finalist to be featured in a documentary hosted by the crew of “In Depth With Laurence Fishburne.” Today we are pleased to announce that we have been selected as the top feature for their series on Distance and E-Learning! Filming of the documentary will begin later this summer. The selection team was impressed and amazed at Edkey's innovation in online learning and our ability to overcome the COVID closure by seamlessly and speedily changing direction amidst the Corona confusion.

Congratulations to the entire Edkey Family of Schools for creating and leading schools that reach and teach students regardless of their learning needs and wherever they are across the state. https://indepthlaurencefishburne.com/

Good Afternoon Edkey Inc. Family,

Our team has been working very hard to get our corporate accreditation, and this morning we received this notification:

"We are pleased to announce Edkey, Inc. is now a Candidate for Accreditation with NCA CASI, NWAC, and SACS CASI."

Once finalized, all Edkey, Inc. schools will be accredited. Currently accredited Edkey, Inc. schools will retain their accreditation through this process.

Thank you to everyone for trusting the process and for your commitment to our students, their families, and the communities we serve.

Mark Plitzuweit, CEO Edkey, Inc.

post_text: Edkey, Inc.'s CEO Mark Plitzuweit presenting perspective on the "Penny for Ed" legislation last week at the Arizona State Capitol. This legislation (if passed) would place an additional 4/10ths of a sales tax, specifically for education, on the 2020 ballot, and allow voters to decide. K-12 would get 75%, or roughly $325 additional per Arizona public school student. The press conference allocated 2 minutes, but he took 3 minutes to get all of the information in. Long story short - if you spend $100 today, if this legislation gets passed through to the voters and then approved, it would increase that same purchase to $100.40.

Don't miss your chance to support students and possibly lower your tax bill.

Make an ECA tax credit donation to Sequoia Charter Schools and change a student's life.

Every dollar goes toward extracurricular activities, and you may choose which school or program you'd like to support. Even better, qualifying taxpayers will receive a dollar-for-dollar credit on their state taxes. The state credit is available to all taxpayers who qualify in the state of Arizona.

Even if you don't live in the district or have a child enrolled in school you can participate, so please share this opportunity with friends and family.

Learn more about ECA and donate online at http://www.sequoiaschools.org/donate today.

Thank you!

The Administrators and Staff of Edkey Inc. and Sequoia Schools

post_text:
Dear Sequoia Pathway Academy Community,

The EdKey board and management team are pleased to announce that Diane Silvia and Nate Lamma are going to serve on the leadership team at Sequoia Pathway Academy. We met with Mr. Lamma and Ms. Silvia this morning and we are working out final details during the fall break. They will be supported by Tamara Becker, assistant superintendent. Ms. Becker will not serve as the interim principal given the return of the school's leaders. The leadership team looks forward to serving the Pathway community when fall break concludes on October 12. Have a wonderful week.

Sincerely,

Mary Gifford, President
EdKey Board
text:
Dear Sequoia Pathway Academy Community,

The EdKey board and management team are pleased to announce that Diane Silvia and Nate Lamma are going to serve on the leadership team at Sequoia Pathway Academy. We met with Mr. Lamma and Ms. Silvia this morning and we are working out final details during the fall break. They will be supported by Tamara Becker, assistant superintendent. Ms. Becker will not serve as the interim principal given the return of the school's leaders. The leadership team looks forward to serving the Pathway community when fall break concludes on October 12. Have a wonderful week.

Sincerely,

Mary Gifford, President
EdKey Board
